hich enables cross-compilation using \\u201cbuild flavors\\u201d.\"),Object(r.a)(\"h3\",null,\"4. Installing dependencies should be reproducible. Every developer should be building the same code.\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"Like Yarn, Buckaroo saves the exact result of dependency resolution to a lock file, which ensures that every deployment uses exactly the same dependencies.\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"Additionally, since all Buckaroo packages build with Buck, it can give reproducible builds. This would not be guaranteed with CMake.\"),Object(r.a)(\"h3\",null,\"5. A dependency should be project-centric. In other words, installing a dependency should not modify your system.\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"Buckaroo is entirely project-local. Only a download cache and some user-settings live outside of your project folder. This guarantees that your \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"https://hackernoon.com/getting-started-with-buck-build-on-travis-ci-d1208d363023\"}),\"CI server\"),\" builds exactly the same code that you do.\"),Object(r.a)(\"h3\",null,\"6. It should be easy to publish new packages.\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"Publishing a Buckaroo package is trivial:\"),Object(r.a)(\"ol\",null,Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ol\"},\"Write a Buck build file to your project\"),Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ol\"},\"Add a buckaroo.json file\"),Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ol\"},\"Create a GitHub release\")),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"That\\u2019s it! See \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"http://buckaroo.readthedocs.io/en/latest/github-package-guide.html\"}),\"this guide\"),\" for more information.\"),Object(r.a)(\"h3\",null,\"7. Require the minimal amount of additional infrastructure, such as servers.\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"Buckaroo leverages existing infrastructure, such as GitHub, so that you don\\u2019t need to host your own server.\"),Object(r.a)(\"h2\",null,\"Conclusion\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"Hopefully this article has explained some of the motivations behind Buckaroo. To summarize:\"),Object(r.a)(\"ul\",null,Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},Object(r.a)(\"p\",{parentName:\"li\"},\"There are many advantages to using a project-centric package manager, such as Buckaroo, in your project.\")),Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},Object(r.a)(\"p\",{parentName:\"li\"},\"Use the system package manager to install tooling and for deployments.\")),Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},Object(r.a)(\"p\",{parentName:\"li\"},\"Git sub-modules is a reasonable option if you have a requirement of minimal tooling.\")),Object(r.a)(\"li\",{parentName:\"ul\"},Object(r.a)(\"p\",{parentName:\"li\"},\"Copy-and-paste is viable for tiny dependencies, such as \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"https://github.com/philsquared/Catch\"}),\"Catch\"),\", but it is still more convenient to use a package manager.\"))),Object(r.a)(\"h3\",null,\"Ready to Get Started? \\ud83e\\udd20\"),Object(r.a)(\"p\",null,\"If you would like try \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"http://buckaroo.pm/\"}),\"Buckaroo\"),\", the best place to start is \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"https://buckaroo.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\"}),\"the documentation\"),\". You can browse the existing packages on \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"http://buckaroo.pm/\"}),\"Buckaroo.pm\"),\" or request more over on \",Object(r.a)(\"a\",l({parentName:\"p\"},{href:\"https://github.com/LoopPerfect/buckaroo-wishlist\"}),\"the wishlist\"),\".\"))}h.isMDXComponent=!0}},[[\"Hyf+\",0,2,1,3,4]]]);","map":{"version":3,"sources":["static/chunks/pages/blog/approaches-to-c-dependency-managment-dc6d4d714ae30d9a6cbe.js"],"names":["_N_E","window","push","Hyf+","module","exports","__webpack_require__","__NEXT_P","hd9w","__webpack_exports__","r","d","frontMatter","MDXContent","_babel_runtime_helpers_esm_defineProperty__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_0__","_babel_runtime_helpers_esm_objectWithoutProperties__WEBPAC