ught.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"A common misconception of C++ is that unlike VM languages, such as Java, the code is not portable across platforms. The truth is that C++ is portable, but in a different way. Whilst Java compiles to a byte-code format, which is platform neutral and can be deployed anywhere, C++ is only portable \", Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"em\", {\n    parentName: \"p\"\n  }, \"before compilation\"), \". This means that to maintain portability, a C++ package manager must provide the source-code for every package, with binaries only as an optimization.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h3\", null, \"4. Dependency installation should be reproducible. Every developer should be building the same code.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"Just as reproducibility is crucial in a build system, it is crucial in any package manager that builds on top. Reproducibility means that the developer can be confident that the code being testing and deployed is what they expected. This prevents subtle bugs from appearing only on some machines, causing production down-time and endless developer frustration!\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h3\", null, \"5. A dependency should be project-centric. In other words, installing a dependency should not modify your system.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"Project-centric solutions are important when writing software because they reduce friction when trying out different dependencies. If adding a dependency requires changing a machine\\u2019s configuration, then developers will be reluctant to try it; something might break and no one wants to have to remember how to reconfigure things afterwards. Even worse, a dependency may be incompatible with a requirement of some system component. A packaging solution should work entirely inside of a project.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h3\", null, \"6. It should be easy to publish new packages.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"When developers contribute their work to the open-source community, or just to colleagues within their organization, they are multiplying the impact of their efforts. We should encourage this! The best way to do so is to make it incredibly easy to publish packages. The process should be self-service; there should be no need for additional infrastructure and you shouldn\\u2019t need to wait for approvals.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h3\", null, \"7. Require the minimal amount of additional infrastructure, such as servers.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"Regardless of how easy it is to deploy, additional infrastructure creates extra costs and adds another point of failure. A good solution will use existing infrastructure wherever possible.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h2\", null, \"Different Approaches\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"OK, let\\u2019s start with a quick round-up of the different approaches.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h3\", null, \"Copy-and-Paste\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"This is the simplest method of dependency management, and it\\u2019s even \", Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"a\", _objectSpread({\n    parentName: \"p\"\n  }, {\n    \"href\": \"https://github.com/SFML/SFML/tree/master/extlibs\"\n  }), \"used by some big projects\"), \"!\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"The problem with this method is that it provides very little actual management. The transitive dependencies of code must be resolved by hand, dependency upgrades are manual and, most crucially, the exact version that was copied must be tracked by the developer. If a binary has been copy-pasted, then cross-compilation is difficult.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"Still, to it\\u2019s credit, the copy-and-paste approach requires no external tools, reproducibility comes for free and it is trivial to set-up.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"h3\", null, \"apt-get (And Similar)\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"Some developers argue that C++ already has a package manager, and that it\\u2019s built into Linux. Using apt-get, many C++ libraries can be installed onto a target machine.\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", null, \"So why not use apt-get? Whilst apt-get is an excellent way to install applications onto your machine, problems occur when using a system package manager for project-level packages:\"), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"ul\", null, Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"li\", {\n    parentName: \"ul\"\n  }, Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", {\n    parentName: \"li\"\n  }, \"It is tied to the operating system. apt-get only works cleanly on Linux, and usually only on Debian environments.\")), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"li\", {\n    parentName: \"ul\"\n  }, Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE_3__[/* mdx */ \"a\"])(\"p\", {\n    parentName: \"li\"\n  }, \"Installing binaries onto your system does not help with cross-compilation.\")), Object(_mdx_js_react__WEBPACK_IMPORTED_MODULE